  "action_id": "432",
  "action_title": "Remove problematic vegetation",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nA before-and-after study from Japan found higher numbers of long-billed plovers Charadrius placidus after the removal of invasive black locust Robinia pseudoacacia.\nA study from Australia found lower mortality of Gould\u2019s petrels Pterodroma leucoptera leucoptera following the removal of most of an island\u2019s (native) bird-lime tree Pisonia umbellifera population, whilst a study from New Zealand found that Chatham Island oystercatchers Haematopus chathamensis could nest in preferable areas following invasive marram grass Ammophila arenaria control.\nA site comparison from the USA found lower densities of several birds in areas with (native) velvet mesquite Prosopis juliflora control."
}
